ote that the tax treatment of stock grants can be complex, and it\'s a good idea to consult with a tax professional to understand your specific tax obligations. The Internal Revenue Service (IRS) is the federal agency responsible for collecting taxes in the United States, and it has published detailed guidance on the tax treatment of various types of stock grants. You can find more information on the IRS website or by contacting the IRS directly.'}
