 seller may counter with a different price or terms. This is where the negotiation process begins. You and the seller will work with your respective agents to come to an agreement on the final sale price and other terms of the transaction.Get a home inspection: Before you finalize the purchase of a home, it is a good idea to have a professional home inspection done. This will help you identify any potential issues with the property, such as structural damage or needed repairs. The inspector will provide you with a report detailing their findings, and you can use this information to negotiate with the seller or make a decision about whether to proceed with the purchase.Finalize the mortgage and close the sale: Once you have agreed on the sale price and any contingencies have been satisfied, it is time to finalize the mortgage and close the sale. This will involve signing a mortgage agreement and paying any closing costs or other fees associated with the transaction. Your real estate agent and mortgage lender will handle most of the details and will be able to guide you through the process."}
